{
  "stem": "7598.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was the imaginary line, the Siegfried Line.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Anyway, one fine morning on May the 10th, 1940, we heard guns.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my father said, don't worry children, it's only a thunderstorm.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He then listened to the radio and realized that the Germans had invaded, or were invading Benelux.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he grew quite pale and he was absolutely horrified.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I remember him rushing to the Diamond Club either to speak to other people or perhaps to get hold of his little fortune of whatever he had and came back and said we were going to move to the seaside.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The reasoning behind that was that in the First World War, parts of Belgium weren't occupied, and the Maginot Line had been built and the Siegfried Line, and somehow the Belgians kidded themselves that because of the imaginary lines they wouldn't be able-- the Germans wouldn't be able to get any further.",
      "word_count": 56
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "There was also an unwritten agreement within the diamond community that if there were trouble, they would all go to Cognac near Bordeaux, where the diamond [INAUDIBLE], diamond center, would evacuate and business would go on as, as usual.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "This was a very important factor for me because later on, when I was separated from my parents, I hung on to this unbelievable hope that we would all get together in Cognac, and if we were lost or separated, this is where we would meet within a few days.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Of course, nothing of this ever materialized.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My father was the eldest of his family.",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
